      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pro-border security side should focus on the economic benefits of a secure border, arguing that increased funding and stricter enforcement will lead to a significant reduction in human trafficking, which is estimated to cost the US economy over $150 billion annually. Additionally, a secure border will allow for more efficient and effective control of the flow of goods, resulting in lower inflation and increased competitiveness in the global market. Furthermore, stricter enforcement will also help to prevent the smuggling of contraband, such as opioids and other illicit substances, which are a major concern for public health and safety.",
